<node id="World Athletics Federation">
  <data key="d0">World Athletics Federation</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The World Athletics Federation, also known as World Athletics, serves as the global governing body for athletics. It holds a comprehensive range of responsibilities, including the organization and management of major athletic events such as the World Athletics Championships. This federation plays a crucial role in setting standards and validating records across various track and field disciplines, ensuring consistency and fairness in competitive athletics worldwide.

The World Athletics Federation is instrumental in overseeing the World Athletics Championship, which is one of its primary responsibilities. The organization also handles record validations, ensuring that all athletic achievements are accurately documented and recognized globally. This oversight helps maintain the integrity of the sport by providing a standardized framework for competition and performance evaluation.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation oversees the World Athletics Championship.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.&lt;SEP&gt;The World Athletics Federation is the governing body overseeing the World Athletics Championship and record validations.</data>
