<node id="Splunk">
  <data key="d0">Splunk</data>
  <data key="d1">software</data>
  <data key="d2">Splunk is a versatile software platform primarily used for monitoring and analyzing machine-generated data. It is employed across various systems, including credit card processing at institutions like 玉山銀行 (Yushan Bank), where it underwent version upgrades. The software's capabilities extend to monitoring firewall events, managing system alerts and incidents, and handling authorization data.

Splunk's functionality includes searching and comparing connection port usage lists with DACL permit lists, as well as analyzing log data. Specific tasks related to onsite operations have been documented from April 7th to April 11th. However, Splunk has also faced issues, such as problems with sending CSV files due to multi-value handling limitations and log data issues reported on August 20, 2025.

During maintenance periods, Splunk undergoes version upgrades and service verification to ensure optimal performance. Its role in monitoring system alerts and incidents highlights its importance in maintaining operational efficiency and security across different systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Splunk is used to collect data such as total volume, top attack types, URIs, IPs, and policies.&lt;SEP&gt;Splunk is a software used in the maintenance process, with weekly onsite operations.&lt;SEP&gt;Splunk is a software system used by Cathay Bank, requiring maintenance and updates.&lt;SEP&gt;Splunk is a software tool that requires user permission adjustments and troubleshooting for connectivity issues with n8n.&lt;SEP&gt;Splunk is a software that underwent various maintenance actions, including IP adjustments and package upgrades.</data>
