<edge source="Taiwan Bank" target="Maintenance Record">
  <data key="d7">12.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The Maintenance Record, pertaining to Taiwan Bank, documents various aspects of maintenance activities performed for this financial institution. The record specifically details the onsite operations carried out by Linda Hsu and other engineers associated with Taiwan Bank. It serves as a comprehensive log of issues encountered during the maintenance process and the actions taken to address them.

Taiwan Bank is identified as the customer for whom the Maintenance Record was created, highlighting its role in receiving these services. The record encompasses all activities conducted as part of Taiwan Bank's maintenance services, ensuring that all relevant operations are documented and tracked. This includes not only the onsite work but also any systems-related issues and their resolutions.

The Maintenance Record is a critical document for Taiwan Bank, providing a detailed account of the maintenance activities performed by their engineers. It ensures transparency and accountability in the maintenance process, helping to maintain the operational integrity of Taiwan Bank's systems and services.&lt;SEP&gt;The Maintenance Record pertains to Taiwan Bank's system issues and details the actions taken by Alfred Yang.&lt;SEP&gt;Taiwan Bank is associated with the maintenance record detailing the adjustments made to their event records.&lt;SEP&gt;The Maintenance Record pertains to the actions taken for Taiwan Bank.&lt;SEP&gt;The Maintenance Record is associated with Taiwan Bank as part of their system maintenance activities.</data>
