<edge source="Maintenance Record" target="Kimi Lee">
  <data key="d7">11.0</data>
  <data key="d8">The relation between Kimi Lee and Maintenance Record involves several distinct entities, each with its own context. Kimi Lee is involved in documenting various maintenance activities across different organizations.

For Kai Jie Life, Kimi Lee documents the maintenance actions taken during sessions in the maintenance record. This indicates a direct role in recording and possibly overseeing the upkeep of systems or equipment specific to this entity.

In the case of Kai Ji Ren Shu, Kimi Lee is documented as one of the engineers handling the maintenance record. This suggests a more technical and hands-on role, likely involving direct involvement in the maintenance activities themselves. Additionally, Kimi Lee handled the maintenance record for Kai Ji Ren Shu, further emphasizing her active participation in this aspect.

Kimi Lee also documents the maintenance actions taken for Kai Chi People Life Insurance in the maintenance record. This shows that her responsibilities extend to documenting maintenance for insurance-related systems or equipment, highlighting her versatility across different sectors within the same organization.

Furthermore, Kimi Lee is documented as one of the engineers involved in the maintenance record for Cathay Life's DB server farm. This indicates a specialized role in maintaining database servers, which are critical components for any organization relying on digital infrastructure.&lt;SEP&gt;Kimi Lee documented the actions taken during the maintenance process in the maintenance record for Kai Jie Ren Shu's systems.&lt;SEP&gt;The Maintenance Record documents the activities performed by Kimi Lee.&lt;SEP&gt;Kimi Lee is documented as an engineer involved in the maintenance record for Kai Ji Ren Shu.</data>
